@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "Main"

@{FG SHINE}Win95_IconRenderer @{FG TEXT}is an external IconRenderer for PowerWindows. It will
make the icons (iconified windows) look like the windows in Windoze95.

Have a look at this @{" image " SYSTEM "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview IconLook.gif SCREEN"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"
@TOC "Main"

You need at least @{FG SHINE}AmigaOS 3.0@{FG TEXT} and @{FG SHINE}PowerWindows V1.0@{FG TEXT} (it might also work
with V0.9.5) to use this IconRenderer.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "LegalStuff" "Legal Stuff"
@TOC "Main"

Win95_IconRenderer is @{FG SHINE}Freeware@{FG TEXT}. Do anything you want with it, but please
register PowerWindows. The first version of PowerWindows was released
more than half a year ago but up to now there have been only three users who
have registered @{b}:( My motivation really starts disappearing :(@{ub}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@TOC "Main"

Use the supplied installation script to copy the IconRenderer to your HD.
If you want to do it by hand then just copy "Win95_IconRenderer" into the
"ExtRoutines" directory of PowerWindows and the guide and preview image 
(which consits of three files: "IconLook", "IconLook.info", "IconLook.gif")
whereever you want.

To activate the new IconRenderer start PW_Prefs. Go to the "External" page,
click on the "External Icon-Renderer" file pop up button and select
"Win95_IconRenderer" in the "ExtRoutines" directory.

After this operation the "External Icon-Renderer" string gadget should look
like this:

	@{FG SHINE}ExtRoutines/Win95_IconRenderer@{FG TEXT}

The Win95_IconRenderer can be configured by adding some arguments to the
text in the string gadget, but first you have to insert a comma (","). E.g.:

	@{FG SHINE}ExtRoutines/Win95_IconRenderer,CENTERTITLE@{FG TEXT}

Go to the @{" Configuration " LINK "Configuration"} chapter to see all possible options.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Configuration" "Configuration"
@TOC "Main"
To configure Win95_IconRenderer you must add some arguments to the "External
Icon-Renderer" string gadget in the "External" page of PW_Prefs. If you want
(or have) to edit the PowerWindows config file by hand, you have to add the
parameters in the line starting with "EXT_IconRenderer=". The parameters
must be specified after a comma (","): <File>,<Parameters> For example:

	@{FG SHINE}ExtRoutines/Win95_IconRenderer,CENTERTITLE@{FG TEXT}

The IconRenderer uses ReadArgs() to parse the arguments, just like all
(or most) CLI/SHELL commands. This is the used argument template:

@{FG SHINE}	FONTNAME=F/K,FONTSIZE=FS/K/N,FONTSTYLE=FST/K/N,
	FONTYOFFSET=FY/K/N,FONTXOFFSET=FX/K/N,BACKCOL=BC/K,
	BORDERWIDTH=BW/K/N,GADGETGAP=GG/K/N,TITLEGAP=TG/K/N,
	PRECISION=P/N,GADPOS=GP/S,SLEEPBRUSH=SB/S,CENTERTITLE=CT/S@{FG TEXT}

If you are not very familiar with argument templates, I'll explain you
the @{" most important things " LINK "parse"}.


@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ


@{FG SHINE}FONTNAME   :@{FG TEXT} Font to be used for title. Don't forget to add "@{b}.font@{ub}".
	     E.g. "@{b}helvetica.font@{ub}"

@{FG SHINE}FONTSIZE   :@{FG TEXT} Size of the font

@{FG SHINE}FONTSTYLE  :@{FG TEXT} Style of the font: @{b}1@{ub} = @{u}underlined@{uu}, @{b}2@{ub} = @{b}bold@{ub}, @{b}4@{ub} = @{i}italic@{ui}.
             It's possible to combine styles. For example: @{b}3@{ub} = @{b}@{u}bold@{uu}@{ub}
             @{b}@{u}underlined@{ub}@{uu} (@{b}1+2@{ub}).

@{FG SHINE}FONTYOFFSET:@{FG TEXT} Can be used to correct the y position of the title

@{FG SHINE}FONTXOFFSET:@{FG TEXT} Can be used to correct the x position of the title

@{FG SHINE}BACKCOL    :@{FG TEXT} 32 Bit RGB value of color to be used for background
	     (which is dark blue by default). You can write it in
	     hexadecimal format: @{b}0xFF7A34@{ub}

@{FG SHINE}BORDERWIDTH:@{FG TEXT} Width (thickness) of the grey border. Should be in the
	     range between @{b}0@{ub} and @{b}2@{ub}.

@{FG SHINE}GADGETGAP  :@{FG TEXT} Gap in pixels between gadgets and other elements

@{FG SHINE}TITLEGAP   :@{FG TEXT} Gap in pixels between title and other elements

@{FG SHINE}PRECISION  :@{FG TEXT} Precision for pen obtaining:

	      @{b}0@{ub} = PRECISION_IMAGE
	     @{b}16@{ub} = PRECISION_ICON
	     @{b}32@{ub} = PRECISION_GUI
	     @{b}-1@{ub} = PRECISION_EXACT (default)

@{FG SHINE}GADPOS     :@{FG TEXT} When activated gadgets will be placed at their correct position
	     (all at the right, just like in Windoze95). By default the
	     close gadget will be placed at the left side.

@{FG SHINE}SLEEPBRUSH :@{FG TEXT} Adds a "sleep brush" at the left side of the icon. Might look
             a little bit strange if GADPOS is not activated.

@{FG SHINE}CENTERTITLE:@{FG TEXT} Center the title

@ENDNODE

@NODE "parse" "The meaning of argument templates"
@TOC "main"

	@{FG SHINE}FONTNAME=F/K,FONTSIZE=FS/K/N,FONTSTYLE=FST/K/N,
	FONTYOFFSET=FY/K/N,FONTXOFFSET=FX/K/N,BACKCOL=BC/K,
	BORDERWIDTH=BW/K/N,GADGETGAP=GG/K/N,TITLEGAP=TG/K/N,
	PRECISION=P/N,GADPOS=GP/S,SLEEPBRUSH=SB/S,CENTERTITLE=CT/S@{FG TEXT}

An argument template appears in the following way ('@{FG SHINE}[@{FG FILL}abc@{FG SHINE}]@{FG TEXT}' means
that this is optional):

KEYWORD@{FG SHINE}[@{FG TEXT}@{FG FILL}=ALIAS_KEYWORD@{FG SHINE}][@{FG TEXT}@{FG FILL}/?@{FG SHINE}][@{FG TEXT}@{FG FILL}/?@{FG SHINE}]@{FG TEXT},KEYWORD2@{FG SHINE}[@{FG TEXT}@{FG FILL}=ALIAS_KEYWORD2@{FG SHINE}][@{FG TEXT}@{FG FILL}/?@{FG SHINE}][@{FG TEXT}@{FG FILL}/?@{FG SHINE}]@{FG TEXT},...



@{b}/K  @{ub} means that if you want to use/change it, you have to write the
     keyword first, put one (or more) spaces or a "=" after it and
     write the value after that. Examples:

     @{FG SHINE}FONTNAME helvetica.font
     FONTNAME=helvetica.font
     F heveltica.font
     F=helvetica.font@{FG TEXT}

@{b}/N  @{ub} means that an integer value is expected. "/N" is very often used
     together with "/K" which means that you have to write the keyword
     first. Examples:

     @{FG SHINE}FONTSIZE=18
     FONTSIZE 18
     FS = 18
     FS 18@{FG TEXT}

@{b}/S  @{ub} means that this is a switch. To activate it simply write the keyword.
     Examples:

     @{FG SHINE}SLEEBRUSH
     SB@{FG TEXT}

@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

Parameters must be separated by one or more spaces:

     @{FG SHINE}FONTNAME=helvetica.font FONTSIZE=28 SLEEPBRUSH CENTERTITLE BW 10@{FG TEXT}

@ENDNODE


